    "description_full": "The objective of this strategy is to outperform SPY with as little coding as possible across most market conditions by dynamically harvesting equity risk premia in calm markets while defensively positioning in stressed, high-volatility conditions. Large left-tail events are avoided by dynamically reducing net equity beta and adding convex volatility exposure when short-term realized volatility spikes.\n\nUnder normal market conditions, the portfolio holds 100 percent long SPY, rotating in rare high-volatility regimes to a defensive mix of approximately 95 percent SH (inverse SPY exposure) and 5 percent UVXY (levered VIX futures exposure) to add crash convexity. The standard deviation risk model, when combined with a trailing stop risk overlay, enables dynamic portfolio rebalancing to enhance overall performance.  ",
